<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12228q"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12228q">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12228q"> 228(q)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> , weepful,</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Me and your mam are full of years, and the hearse from Capel Sion will soon take us home to the Big Man&apos;s Palace &mdash; a home, Tomos, where we will wear White Shirts, and where there is no old rent to pay. Tomos, Tomos, <mark>weepful</mark> you will be when I am up above. Little Great One, keep an eye on Tomos. Be with your son in Capel Sion. Amen. <small> Caradoc Evans, <a name="EVAN" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EVAN"><cite title="source">My People</cite></a> (1915) 27 [A Heifer without blemish]</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Left margin  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c12219e" href="c12all.htm#c12219e">VI.C.12:219(e)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
